Philippine Stocks: Aboitiz Power, Globe Telecom, Jollibee, PLDT

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-04-01T04:41:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/philippine-stocks-aboitiz-power-globe-telecom-jollibee-pldt.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 1.8 percent to
4,129.54, completing a 6.6 percent gain this week. It’s the
benchmark’s biggest weekly gain since March 2009. The gauge lost
3.5 percent in the three months to yesterday, the first slump
since the fourth quarter of 2008.  Aboitiz Power Corp. (AP)  , owner of power plants and
distributors, climbed 1.7 percent to 30.50 pesos, the highest
since March 11. The company said a unit agreed to buy out its
partner in a hydro-power plant in a transaction valued at $30
million.  Aboitiz Equity Ventures Inc. (AEV)  , Aboitiz Power’s
parent, advanced 2.6 percent to 42.15 pesos, the sharpest gain
since Feb. 28.  Globe Telecom Inc. (GLO)  , the second-biggest provider of
mobile phone services, sank 3.5 percent to 860 pesos, the
sharpest loss since March 4 and ending a three-day, 28 percent
rally. Bigger rival  Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co. (TEL)  , also known as PLDT, said yesterday that Digital
Telecommunications Philippines Inc. (DGTL PM) will not stop its
unlimited calls and text message mobile phone service.  PLDT, which offered to buy Digital on March 29, gained 1.4
percent to 2,356 pesos. Digital Telecom closed unchanged at 1.54
pesos.  Jollibee Foods Corp. (JFC)  , the nation’s biggest
restaurant operator, jumped 4.2 percent to 90.90 pesos, the
highest since Nov. 15. The company said it bought an additional
stake in Chow Fun Holdings LLC for $3.24 million, raising its
holding in the U.S. restaurant operator to 80.6 percent from 12
percent previously. Chow Fun is the developer and owner of Jinja
Bar and Bistro in  New Mexico , according to a stock exchange
filing by Manila-based Jollibee.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
